===Etymology===
From {{OF.}} ''[[espoillier]]'', from {{L.}} [[spoliare]].

===Verb===
{{en-verb|spoils|spoiling|'''[[spoiled]] '''or''' [[spoilt]]'''}}

# {{transitive}} To [[ruin]].
# {{transitive}} To [[coddle]] or [[pamper]] to excess.
# {{intransitive}} Of food, to become bad, [[sour]] or [[rancid]].

